  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "If you're receiving Likes or engagement from people in India despite targeting your ad campaign solely to people in San Francisco (SF), there are several potential reasons for this discrepancy:\n\n1. **VPN Usage**: Some users in India may be using VPNs (Virtual Private Networks) to mask their actual location. If their VPN shows an IP address in SF, they may appear as if they are in your target location and thus see and engage with your ad.\n\n2. **Misconfigured Targeting**: Double-check your ad campaign settings to ensure the location targeting is correctly set to SF. Sometimes, errors in setting up the campaign (e.g., selecting \"people in or recently in SF\" instead of \"people living in SF\") can lead to unintended audiences seeing your ad.\n\n3. **Audience Expansion**: Some platforms, like Facebook or Instagram, may automatically expand your audience to include people with similar interests outside your target location if they believe it will improve performance. You can often disable this feature in your campaign settings.\n\n4. **Travelers or Relocated Users**: People who recently traveled to SF or moved from SF to India might still be included in your target audience if they meet the criteria based on their profile information or recent activity.\n\n5. **Algorithm Errors**: Platforms sometimes make mistakes in identifying user locations due to outdated or inaccurate data.\n\n6. **Fake Accounts or Bots**: Some Likes may come from fake accounts or bots that are not accurately tied to a specific location.\n\n7. **Cross-Border Targeting**: If your campaign is set to target \"SF and surrounding areas,\" some platforms may interpret this broadly and include users from other regions who may have traveled or interacted with SF-related content.\n\n### How to Fix It:\n- **Review Ad Settings**: Ensure your campaign is set to target only people living in SF, not those who have recently been in SF or are traveling there.\n- **Exclude Regions**: If possible, exclude specific countries or regions (like India) from your targeting to minimize unwanted engagement.\n- **Disable Audience Expansion**: Turn off any audience expansion features in your campaign settings.\n- **Monitor Engagement**: Regularly check the demographics of who is engaging with your ad and adjust targeting as needed.\n- **Report the Issue**: If the problem persists, contact the ad platform's support team to investigate and resolve the issue.\n\nBy addressing these factors, you can better control who sees and engages with your ad campaign.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
